history.content: None. You can P/NP every class in a semester as long as you graduate with more than 2/3 of your units graded.

children.subject: Ah ok not for EECS specifically because you won't get credit for the class and would have to retake it anyway, but if you're fine with that, 100% sure you can P/NP all classes in a semester
@Kunal - not sure about that. I don't think you can P/NP all your classes in a semester. Better if an instructor could clarify this.
